main event: Multiple bright-colored objects observed over Indianapolis, Indiana on 23 March 1960.
interesting points: The objects looked like lights, some the size of a dime at arm's length, The objects blinked on and off, The sighting lasted approximately 3/4 minutes, The objects were first seen in the NW and moved SE, The report suggests that the observed objects may have been natural phenomena.
witness description: Male, one a photographer age 42, another a male aged 32
